TY  - JOUR
T1  - Learning the Wealth of Nations
AU  - Buera, Francisco J.
AU  - Monge-Naranjo, Alexander
AU  - Primiceri, Giorgio E.
Y1  - 2011/01/01
PY  - 2011
DA  - 2011/01/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA8299
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 1
EP  - 45
VL  - 79
IS  - 1
KW  - Learning
KW  - dynamic of policies
KW  - economic growth
KW  - market-oriented policies
KW  - neighborhood effects
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA8299
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We study the evolution of market-oriented policies over time and across countries. We consider a model in which own and neighbors' past experiences influence policy choices through their effect on policymakers' beliefs. We estimate the model using a large panel of countries and find that it fits a large fraction of the policy choices observed in the postwar data, including the slow adoption of liberal policies. Our model also predicts that there would be reversals to state intervention if nowadays the world was hit by a shock of the size of the Great Depression.
ER  - 

