TY  - JOUR
T1  - Axiomatic Foundations of Multiplier Preferences
AU  - Strzalecki, Tomasz
Y1  - 2011/01/01
PY  - 2011
DA  - 2011/01/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA8155
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 47
EP  - 73
VL  - 79
IS  - 1
KW  - Ambiguity aversion
KW  - model uncertainty
KW  - robustness
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA8155
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - This paper axiomatizes the robust control criterion of multiplier preferences introduced by Hansen and Sargent (2001). The axiomatization relates multiplier preferences to other classes of preferences studied in decision theory, in particular, the variational preferences recently introduced by Maccheroni, Marinacci, and Rustichini (2006a). This paper also establishes a link between the parameters of the multiplier criterion and the observable behavior of the agent. This link enables measurement of the parameters on the basis of observable choice data and provides a useful tool for applications.
ER  - 

